Valmie (VMRI) is a Big Hit at the Offshore Technology Conference in Houston





Valmie (VMRI) is Awarded FAA 333 Exemption to Fly in National Airspace




 
 
 
 
 



BREAKINGNEWS
 
 
 
 





Here is How AeroLift eXpress Works
There are thousands of oil drilling platforms worldwide that are near shore. When these break down, the cost of standing still is enormous, and many times it is over a small part like a seal or an O-ring. Until now, these companies have been forced to hire an expensive helicopter or a slow workboat to deliver these parts. AeroLift eXpress is tailored to quickly deliver these parts, via drone, for a fraction of the cost—producing a nice revenue stream for VMRI.






 
 
 

 
 

 
 

 
 
 
 

 
 
 
 



“Drones could do for physical transportation what the Internet did for the flow of information.”– Gerald Hammack, President | CEO
 
 
 
 



Why Valmie?The commitment we have to our investors and end users is focused on making drone technology safe, reliable, and cost effective. As drone technology continues to move into the mainstream market, Valmie anticipates taking a leadership position in the industry by delivering an enhanced user experience. Valmie’s promise is in reach and its commitment will maximize company growth for its investors.
 
 
 
 




 
 

 
 
 



 
 
 



